# YouTube Knowledge Ingestion

When ingesting knowledge from YouTube sources:

- Start with Firecrawl scrape on the watch URL.
- If the scrape lacks spoken transcript text, search the web for the exact video title plus the channel name using Firecrawl with `--scrape`.
- If the title-based search still looks weak, retry with the video ID plus `YouTube` and the channel name.
- Use transcript-bearing search results when the watch-page scrape is metadata-only.
- Treat either a `## Transcript` section or a `Search transcript` block as usable transcript evidence.
- If search still does not expose transcript text, try Firecrawl interact to open the transcript UI.
- Do not store durable lessons from title, comments, recommendations, or metadata alone.
- If transcript evidence is unavailable, skip the source or leave it queued for later review.
